people_also_ask.question: What happened in Pennsylvania in 2011?
people_also_ask.answer_source: 4th Anniversary of the Flooding from Tropical Storm Lee
people_also_ask.answer_html: During the first week of September in 2011, heavy rain from the remnants of Tropical Storm Lee, led to historic flooding in the Mid-Atlantic Region and especially Central Pennsylvania. The flooding was exacerbated by the saturated soil from previous heavy rain, just a week earlier from Hurricane Irene.

people_also_ask.answer_html: UPPER MAKEFIELD TWP., Pennsylvania -- A search resumed Monday for a 9-month-old boy and his 2-year-old sister after they and their mother were swept away in a flash flood in Bucks County, Pennsylvania, on Saturday while driving with other family members to a barbecue, officials said.Jul 17, 2023
